</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ledoyer" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis armata" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both of which have a known distribution that is so far confined to Madagascar. 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinogradov, GM" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the South African Museum" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" pagination="39 - 88" refId="B202" refString="Vinogradov, GM, 2004. Near-bottom and pelagic gammaridean amphipods in the western Indian Ocean. Annals of the South African Museum 112: 39 - 88" title="Near-bottom and pelagic gammaridean amphipods in the western Indian Ocean." volume="112" year="2004">Vinogradov (2004)</bibRefCitation>
does not justify his generic placement of the species, but presumably it was due to the absence of a molar, which 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the type of the genus, is now known to have. Nonetheless, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits characters which fit within the diagnosis of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublittoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublittoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublittoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ledoyer" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis armata" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: molar absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ledoyer" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis armata" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; mandible palp broadened medially in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, margins subparallel in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ledoyer" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis armata" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; pereopod 5 basis almost linear in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, broadly expanded posteriorly in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ledoyer" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis armata" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; uropod 3 rami subequal in length in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, inner ramus distinctly shorter than outer in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ledoyer" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis armata" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; telson length 1.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
width in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 1.2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
width in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Ledoyer" baseAuthorityYear="1986" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis armata" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis armata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublittoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublittoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublittoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also easily be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of a molar (present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); the shape of gnathopod 1, which is much more elongate and slender in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and the shape of pereopod 7 basis, which has a long, thin posterodistal lobe in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Vinogradov" authorityYear="2004" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sublitoralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis sublitoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared to the posteroventrally excavate corner of the pereopod 7 basis in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1926" class="Malacostraca" family="Scopelocheiridae" genus="Scopelocheiropsis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis" order="Amphipoda" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Scopelocheiropsis abyssalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
